- **Latest Version of Spring Data Elasticsearch**: As of my last update, the latest version is 4.5.2.

- **CLI Commands**:
  - To create a new project with Spring Initializr including Spring Data Elasticsearch: `curl https://start.spring.io/starter.zip -d dependencies=web,data-elasticsearch -o spring-data-elasticsearch-project.zip`
  - To run the application: `./mvnw spring-boot:run`

- **Key Configuration Options**:
  - `application.properties` or `application.yml`: Configure Elasticsearch connection details.
    ```properties
    spring.elasticsearch.rest.uris=http://localhost:9200
    ```
  - Entity Mapping: Define entity classes with annotations like `@Document`, `@Field`.
    ```java
    @Document(indexName = "example")
    public class ExampleEntity {
        @Id
        private String id;

        @Field(type = FieldType.Text)
        private String name;

        // Getters and setters
    }
    ```
  - Repository Interface: Extend `ElasticsearchRepository` for basic CRUD operations.
    ```java
    public interface ExampleRepository extends ElasticsearchRepository<ExampleEntity, String> {
        List<ExampleEntity> findByName(String name);
    }
    ```

- **Additional Tips**:
  - Ensure Elasticsearch is running and accessible at the specified URI.
  - Use `@Query` annotation for complex queries if needed.
  - Implement custom converters for data serialization/deserialization.
